name: Anna Moeller Poetess, Painter May 9, 2021
description: is an artist in painting, drawing, sculpture, video, performance, photography and installation. Moeller creates artworks that are both playful and critical of the relationship between humans and technology. Her work has been described as having a “playful, mischievous quality that is occasionally shot through with a sense of dread about the future.” Moeller is currently a professor at the CCofA in Los Angeles, where she lives and works. https://www.instagram.com/evartology/
